#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:919
msgid "vtkArrayDispatch::DispatchByArray"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:921
msgid ""
"This family of dispatchers takes a `vtkTypeList` of explicit array types to "
"use during dispatching. They should only be used when an array's exact type "
"is restricted. If dispatching multiple arrays and only one has such type "
"restrictions, use `vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays` (or a filtered version) for the "
"unrestricted arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:928
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::DispatchByArray`: Single dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:929
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2ByArray`: Double dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:930
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch3ByArray`: Triple dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:932
msgid ""
"__Arrays considered__: All arrays explicitly listed in the parameter lists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:934
msgid ""
"__Restrictions__: Array must be explicitly listed in the dispatcher's type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:936
msgid "__Usecase__: Used when one or more arrays have known implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:940
msgid ""
"An example here would be a filter that processes an input array of some "
"integral type and produces either a `vtkDoubleArray` or a `vtkFloatArray`, "
"depending on some condition. Since the input array's implementation is "
"unknown (it comes from outside the filter), we'll rely on a ValueType-"
"filtered version of `vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays` for its type. However, we "
"know the output array is either `vtkDoubleArray` or `vtkFloatArray`, so "
"we'll want to be sure to apply that restriction:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:948
msgid ""
"// input has an unknown implementation, but an integral ValueType.\n"
"vtkDataArray *input = ...;\n"
"\n"
"// Output is always either vtkFloatArray or vtkDoubleArray:\n"
"vtkDataArray *output = someCondition ? vtkFloatArray::New()\n"
"                                     : vtkDoubleArray::New();\n"
"\n"
"// Define the valid ArrayTypes for input by filtering\n"
"// vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays to remove non-integral types:\n"
"typedef typename vtkArrayDispatch::FilterArraysByValueType\n"
"  <\n"
"  vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays,\n"
"  vtkArrayDispatch::Integrals\n"
"  >::Result InputTypes;\n"
"\n"
"// For output, create a new vtkTypeList with the only two possibilities:\n"
"typedef vtkTypeList::Create<vtkFloatArray, vtkDoubleArray> OutputTypes;\n"
"\n"
"// Typedef the dispatch to a more manageable name:\n"
"typedef vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2ByArray\n"
"  <\n"
"  InputTypes,\n"
"  OutputTypes\n"
"  > MyDispatch;\n"
"\n"
"// Execute the dispatch:\n"
"MyDispatch::Execute(input, output, someWorker);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:980
msgid "vtkArrayDispatch::DispatchByValueType"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:982
msgid ""
"This family of dispatchers takes a vtkTypeList of ValueTypes for each array "
"and restricts dispatch to only arrays in vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays that have "
"one of the specified value types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:987
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::DispatchByValueType`: Single dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:988
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2ByValueType`: Double dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:989
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch3ByValueType`: Triple dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:991
#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1101
msgid ""
"__Arrays considered__: All arrays in `vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays` that meet "
"the ValueType requirements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:994
msgid ""
"__Restrictions__: Arrays that do not satisfy the ValueType requirements are "
"eliminated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:997
msgid ""
"__Usecase__: Used when one or more of the dispatched arrays has an unknown "
"implementation, but a known (or restricted) ValueType."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1002
msgid ""
"Here we'll consider a filter that processes three arrays. The first is a "
"complete unknown. The second is known to hold `unsigned char`, but we don't "
"know the implementation. The third holds either `double`s or `float`s, but "
"its implementation is also unknown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1007
msgid ""
"// Complete unknown:\n"
"vtkDataArray *array1 = ...;\n"
"// Some array holding unsigned chars:\n"
"vtkDataArray *array2 = ...;\n"
"// Some array holding either floats or doubles:\n"
"vtkDataArray *array3 = ...;\n"
"\n"
"// Typedef the dispatch to a more manageable name:\n"
"typedef vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch3ByValueType\n"
"  <\n"
"  vtkArrayDispatch::AllTypes,\n"
"  vtkTypeList::Create<unsigned char>,\n"
"  vtkArrayDispatch::Reals\n"
"  > MyDispatch;\n"
"\n"
"// Execute the dispatch:\n"
"MyDispatch::Execute(array1, array2, array3, someWorker);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1029
msgid "vtkArrayDispatch::DispatchByArrayWithSameValueType"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1031
msgid ""
"This family of dispatchers takes a `vtkTypeList` of ArrayTypes for each "
"array and restricts dispatch to only consider arrays from those typelists, "
"with the added requirement that all dispatched arrays share a ValueType."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1036
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2ByArrayWithSameValueType`: Double dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1037
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch3ByArrayWithSameValueType`: Triple dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1039
msgid ""
"__Arrays considered__: All arrays in the explicit typelists that meet the "
"ValueType requirements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1042
#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1104
msgid ""
"__Restrictions__: Combinations of arrays with differing ValueTypes are "
"eliminated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1045
msgid ""
"__Usecase__: When one or more arrays are known to belong to a restricted set "
"of ArrayTypes, and all arrays are known to share the same ValueType, "
"regardless of implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1051
msgid ""
"Let's consider a double array dispatch, with `array1` known to be one of "
"four common array types (AOS `float`, `double`, `int`, and `vtkIdType` "
"arrays), and the other is a complete unknown, although we know that it holds "
"the same ValueType as `array1`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1056
msgid ""
"// AOS float, double, int, or vtkIdType array:\n"
"vtkDataArray *array1 = ...;\n"
"// Unknown implementation, but the ValueType matches array1:\n"
"vtkDataArray *array2 = ...;\n"
"\n"
"// array1's possible types:\n"
"typedef vtkTypeList;:Create<vtkFloatArray, vtkDoubleArray,\n"
"                            vtkIntArray, vtkIdTypeArray> Array1Types;\n"
"\n"
"// array2's possible types:\n"
"typedef typename vtkArrayDispatch::FilterArraysByValueType\n"
"  <\n"
"  vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays,\n"
"  vtkTypeList::Create<float, double, int, vtkIdType>\n"
"  > Array2Types;\n"
"\n"
"// Typedef the dispatch to a more manageable name:\n"
"typedef vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2ByArrayWithSameValueType\n"
"  <\n"
"  Array1Types,\n"
"  Array2Types\n"
"  > MyDispatch;\n"
"\n"
"// Execute the dispatch:\n"
"MyDispatch::Execute(array1, array2, someWorker);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1086
msgid "vtkArrayDispatch::DispatchBySameValueType"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1088
msgid ""
"This family of dispatchers takes a single `vtkTypeList` of ValueType and "
"restricts dispatch to only consider arrays from `vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays` "
"with those ValueTypes, with the added requirement that all dispatched arrays "
"share a ValueType."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1094
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2BySameValueType`: Double dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1095
msgid "`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch3BySameValueType`: Triple dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1096
msgid ""
"`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2SameValueType`: Double dispatch using "
"`vtkArrayDispatch::AllTypes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1098
msgid ""
"`vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch3SameValueType`: Triple dispatch using "
"`vtkArrayDispatch::AllTypes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1107
msgid ""
"__Usecase__: When one or more arrays are known to belong to a restricted set "
"of ValueTypes, and all arrays are known to share the same ValueType, "
"regardless of implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1113
msgid ""
"Let's consider a double array dispatch, with `array1` known to be one of "
"four common ValueTypes (`float`, `double`, `int`, and `vtkIdType` arrays), "
"and `array2` known to have the same ValueType as `array1`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1117
msgid ""
"// Some float, double, int, or vtkIdType array:\n"
"vtkDataArray *array1 = ...;\n"
"// Unknown, but the ValueType matches array1:\n"
"vtkDataArray *array2 = ...;\n"
"\n"
"// The allowed ValueTypes:\n"
"typedef vtkTypeList::Create<float, double, int, vtkIdType> ValidValueTypes;\n"
"\n"
"// Typedef the dispatch to a more manageable name:\n"
"typedef vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2BySameValueType\n"
"  <\n"
"  ValidValueTypes\n"
"  > MyDispatch;\n"
"\n"
"// Execute the dispatch:\n"
"MyDispatch::Execute(array1, array2, someWorker);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1138
msgid "Advanced Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1140
msgid "Accessing Memory Buffers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1142
msgid ""
"Despite the thin `vtkGenericDataArray` API's nice feature that compilers can "
"optimize memory accesses, sometimes there are still legitimate reasons to "
"access the underlying memory buffer. This can still be done safely by "
"providing overloads to your worker's `operator()` method. For instance, "
"`vtkDataArray::DeepCopy` uses a generic implementation when mixed array "
"implementations are used, but has optimized overloads for copying between "
"arrays with the same ValueType and implementation. The worker for this "
"dispatch is shown below as an example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1151
msgid ""
"// Copy tuples from src to dest:\n"
"struct DeepCopyWorker\n"
"{\n"
"  // AoS --> AoS same-type specialization:\n"
"  template <typename ValueType>\n"
"  void operator()(vtkAOSDataArrayTemplate<ValueType> *src,\n"
"                  vtkAOSDataArrayTemplate<ValueType> *dst)\n"
"  {\n"
"    std::copy(src->Begin(), src->End(), dst->Begin());\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  // SoA --> SoA same-type specialization:\n"
"  template <typename ValueType>\n"
"  void operator()(vtkSOADataArrayTemplate<ValueType> *src,\n"
"                  vtkSOADataArrayTemplate<ValueType> *dst)\n"
"  {\n"
"    vtkIdType numTuples = src->GetNumberOfTuples();\n"
"    for (int comp; comp < src->GetNumberOfComponents(); ++comp)\n"
"      {\n"
"      ValueType *srcBegin = src->GetComponentArrayPointer(comp);\n"
"      ValueType *srcEnd = srcBegin + numTuples;\n"
"      ValueType *dstBegin = dst->GetComponentArrayPointer(comp);\n"
"\n"
"      std::copy(srcBegin, srcEnd, dstBegin);\n"
"      }\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  // Generic implementation:\n"
"  template <typename Array1T, typename Array2T>\n"
"  void operator()(Array1T *src, Array2T *dst)\n"
"  {\n"
"    vtkDataArrayAccessor<Array1T> s(src);\n"
"    vtkDataArrayAccessor<Array2T> d(dst);\n"
"\n"
"    typedef typename vtkDataArrayAccessor<Array2T>::APIType DestType;\n"
"\n"
"    vtkIdType tuples = src->GetNumberOfTuples();\n"
"    int comps = src->GetNumberOfComponents();\n"
"\n"
"    for (vtkIdType t = 0; t < tuples; ++t)\n"
"      {\n"
"      for (int c = 0; c < comps; ++c)\n"
"        {\n"
"        d.Set(t, c, static_cast<DestType>(s.Get(t, c)));\n"
"        }\n"
"      }\n"
"  }\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1202
msgid "Putting It All Together"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1204
msgid ""
"Now that we've explored the new tools introduced with VTK 7.1 that allow "
"efficient, implementation agnostic array access, let's take another look at "
"the `calcMagnitude` example from before and identify the key features of the "
"implementation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1209
msgid ""
"// Modern implementation of calcMagnitude using new concepts in VTK 7.1:\n"
"struct CalcMagnitudeWorker\n"
"{\n"
"  template <typename VectorArray, typename MagnitudeArray>\n"
"  void operator()(VectorArray *vectors, MagnitudeArray *magnitude)\n"
"  {\n"
"    VTK_ASSUME(vectors->GetNumberOfComponents() == 3);\n"
"    VTK_ASSUME(magnitude->GetNumberOfComponents() == 1);\n"
"\n"
"    vtkDataArrayAccessor<VectorArray> v(vectors);\n"
"    vtkDataArrayAccessor<MagnitudeArray> m(magnitude);\n"
"\n"
"    vtkIdType numVectors = vectors->GetNumberOfTuples();\n"
"    for (vtkIdType tupleIdx = 0; tupleIdx < numVectors; ++tupleIdx)\n"
"      {\n"
"      m.Set(tupleIdx, 0, std::sqrt(v.Get(tupleIdx, 0) * v.Get(tupleIdx, 0) "
"+\n"
"                                   v.Get(tupleIdx, 1) * v.Get(tupleIdx, 1) "
"+\n"
"                                   v.Get(tupleIdx, 2) * v.Get(tupleIdx, "
"2)));\n"
"      }\n"
"  }\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"void calcMagnitude(vtkDataArray *vectors, vtkDataArray *magnitude)\n"
"{\n"
"  CalcMagnitudeWorker worker;\n"
"  typedef vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2ByValueType\n"
"    <\n"
"      vtkArrayDispatch::AllTypes,\n"
"      vtkArrayDispatch::Reals\n"
"    > Dispatcher;\n"
"\n"
"  if (!Dispatcher::Execute(vectors, magnitude, worker))\n"
"    {\n"
"    worker(vectors, magnitude); // vtkDataArray fallback\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1248
msgid "This implementation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1250
msgid ""
"Uses dispatch restrictions to reduce the number of instantiated templated "
"worker functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1252
msgid "Assuming 26 types are in `vtkArrayDispatch::Arrays` (13 AOS + 13 SOA)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1253
msgid "The first array is unrestricted. All 26 array types are considered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1254
msgid ""
"The second array is restricted to `float` or `double` ValueTypes, which "
"translates to 4 array types (one each, SOA and AOS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1256
msgid ""
"26 * 4 = 104 possible combinations exist. We've eliminated 26 * 22 = 572 "
"combinations that an unrestricted double-dispatch would have generated (it "
"would create 676 instantiations)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1259
msgid ""
"The calculation is still carried out at `double` precision when the "
"ValueType restrictions are not met."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1261
msgid ""
"Just because we don't want those other 572 cases to have special code "
"generated doesn't necessarily mean that we wouldn't want them to run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1263
msgid ""
"Thanks to `vtkDataArrayAccessor`, we have a fallback implementation that "
"reuses our templated worker code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1265
msgid ""
"In this case, the dispatch is really just a fast-path implementation for "
"floating point output types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1267
msgid ""
"The performance should be identical to iterating through raw memory buffers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1268
msgid ""
"The `vtkGenericDataArray` API is transparent to the compiler. The "
"specialized instantiations of `operator()` can be heavily optimized since "
"the memory access patterns are known and well-defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1271
msgid ""
"Using `VTK_ASSUME` tells the compiler that the arrays have known strides, "
"allowing further compile-time optimizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../Doxygen/ArrayDispatch-VTK-7-1.md:1274
msgid ""
"Hopefully this has convinced you that the `vtkArrayDispatch` and related "
"tools are worth using to create flexible, efficient, typesafe "
"implementations for your work with VTK. Please direct any questions you may "
"have on the subject to the [VTK Discourse][] forum."
msgstr ""
